The paper discusses the use of linear precoders in massive MU-MIMO downlink, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed feedforward architectures and decentralized precoders involve communication networks and system control, which are relevant to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions implementation results on a multi-GPU system, which could be classified under computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
